creator: daniel.sand@pixelpark.com
text:
Hello,

Mostly everytime it fails on linking. 
Previous Versions, like 2.0.52 and below their are no problems.

never seen such a weird error in the linking process.

creator: jorton@redhat.com
text:
You need to build a shared copy of gdbm if you want to link shared libraries
against it; try rebuilding gdbm passing --enable-shared on the configure line.
Alternatively drop gdbm support from httpd unless you need it - pass
"--without-gdbm" on the httpd configure line.

creator: daniel.sand@pixelpark.com
text:
(In reply to comment #1)
> You need to build a shared copy of gdbm if you want to link shared libraries
> against it; try rebuilding gdbm passing --enable-shared on the configure line.
> Alternatively drop gdbm support from httpd unless you need it - pass
> "--without-gdbm" on the httpd configure line.

thx for the quick answer, buuuuuuttttt...

first of all. We're trying to build an almost static apache bin.
So it's needed that gdbm is static.
second it worked the last releases.... so... er.... hello bug 
third, yes we need gdbm support and if you dont support it anymore, plz make it
public.

creator: jorton@redhat.com
text:
You can use --disable-shared to prevent building the shared libraries at all,
but then you won't be able to build the shared modules either I believe.  Please
take up further discussion on users@httpd.apache.org; there is no bug identified
here.
